{
  "texts": [
    "However, we recognise a perceived need by the community to extend, in the future, the effort of the EOSC Task Force on Semantic Interoperability to focus on: (a) understanding how semantic artefacts should be used productively in and for research; (b) how data stewards can efficiently and effectively use these artefacts in metadata specification and metadata curation workflows; and (c) how to bring data producers, publishers, researchers, to adopt them.",
    "This section presents the methodology followed to identify the dimensions and related features of the maturity model and analyse the catalogues of semantic artefacts.",
    "The process was divided into five steps, described in the following subsections.",
    "analysis of existing literature.",
    "We involved all the members of the EOSC Task Force on Semantic Interoperability, which included several experts on the topic with very heterogeneous backgrounds, to provide us with relevant material related to at least one of the two aspects of interest for our study, i.e., (1) definitions of catalogues of semantic artefacts and (2) dimensions that can be used to measure the maturity of such catalogues."
  ]
}